## Best Practices

### DO ✅

```yaml
# Use descriptive names
john:
  email: john@example.com

published_article:
  title: Published Article
  status: published

# Use ERB for dates
created_at: <%= 1.week.ago %>

# Reference associations
article:
  user: john

# Include realistic data
body: This is a realistic article body with enough content to pass validations

# Use different states
draft:
  status: draft
published:
  status: published
archived:
  status: archived
```

### DON'T ❌

```yaml
# Don't use auto-incrementing IDs
# Rails handles IDs automatically

# Don't duplicate data unnecessarily
# Reference associations instead

# Don't forget required fields
article:
  title: Missing required body field!

# Don't use unrealistic data
email: test  # Not a valid email
body: x  # Too short

# Don't hardcode dates
created_at: 2025-01-01  # Use ERB: <%= 1.week.ago %>
```

