## Alternatives to Fixtures

### FactoryBot (More flexibility)

```ruby
# Gemfile
gem 'factory_bot_rails', group: [:development, :test]

# test/factories/users.rb
FactoryBot.define do
  factory :user do
    sequence(:email) { |n| "user#{n}@example.com" }
    first_name { "Test" }
    last_name { "User" }
    password { "password" }
  end
end

# Usage
user = create(:user)
article = create(:article, user: user)
```

### When to Use Fixtures vs Factories

**Use Fixtures when:**
- Simple test data needs
- Fast test suite (fixtures are faster)
- Standard Rails approach

**Use Factories when:**
- Complex object creation
- Need randomized data
- Creating variations of objects
- Need callbacks during creation

